Description:
SEO Manager Job Opportunity


We are looking for a SEO manager who will be responsible for developing and implementing an organic search strategy to ensure that : Our sites and offering services content ranks highly in search engines, grows organic traffic, and increases overall conversion rates and revenue. This position will be responsible for maximizing the visibility of all organic search results across all platforms including mobile, tablet and desktop.

The qualifications we are seeking on the ideal candidate as well as the acceptable requirements are as following:

Requirements:
Define SEO forecasts, monitoring, and reporting on search engine KPI's and their impact on defined business goals;
Ensure that optimization opportunities are identified and initiatives taken to increase search engine ranking;
Evaluate existing and proposed sites for SEO optimization and provide clear actionable solutions for site improvement;
Monitor consumer search trends and identify new opportunities for optimization;
Make recommendations on key word selection;

Compensation:
$50,000 - $60,000 depending on experience
All candidates interested in this position should reply with their most up-to-date resume and letter of interest to hr@brivincorp.com. Please, include examples of work or past projects you have worked on.

Note: If you are providing examples of your work, please outline what your role and scope of work was on the project.This is a full-time and onsite position in our North Miami, FL office.
